<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>RADIATOR/COOLING SYSTEM SERVICE MANUAL - PROSTAR&#8482; - COOLING PACKAGE COMPONENTS - FAN SHROUD</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="5">
        <title>FAN SHROUD</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fan Shroud - Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The A/C condenser must be repositioned before the bottom fan shroud can be removed.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove nut from P-clamps securing the A/C lines to the top channel plate (
                    <hotlnk document="s12021_14.xml" xrefid="f1202104">Figure 8, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two nuts and washers from the A/C condenser top mount brackets (
                    <hotlnk document="s12021_14.xml" xrefid="f1202104">Figure 8, Items 6 and 7</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully remove the A/C condenser by raising the A/C condenser over the top of the
                    cooling package and securing the A/C condenser out of the way (
                    <hotlnk document="s12021_14.xml" xrefid="f1202105">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two top mount nuts and one bottom mount bolt from the surge tank (
                    <hotlnk document="s12021_13.xml" xrefid="f1202103">Figure 7, Items 2 and 3</hotlnk>). Secure surge
                    tank away from fan shroud.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1202106" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202106.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Left Charge Air Cooler Hose</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LEFT CHARGE AIR COOLER HOSE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPRING CLAMPS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen two spring clamps and remove the left charge air cooler hose.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1202107" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202107.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Top Fan Shroud</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TOP FAN SHROUD WASHERS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TOP FAN SHROUD MOUNT BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. PLASTIC HOLD TABS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BOTTOM FAN SHROUD</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. TOP FAN SHROUD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two bolts and washers from the top fan shroud.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Beginning with the top plastic hold tab, release three plastic hold tabs and remove the
                    top fan shroud.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1202108" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202108.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Radiator Fan</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FAN DRIVE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RADIATOR FAN</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WASHERS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. LOCK WASHERS</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. RADIATOR FAN MOUNT NUTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove six nuts, lock washers, and washers from the radiator fan.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the radiator fan from the fan drive.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1202109" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202109.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Left Radiator Stay Rod</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. STAY ROD WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. STAY ROD MOUNT NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. STAY ROD</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. STAY ROD MOUNT BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. STAY ROD MOUNT BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bolts, washers, and nuts from stay rods and stay rod mount brackets, on both
                    sides of the radiator.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1202110" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202110.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Bottom Fan Shroud</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BOTTOM FAN SHROUD WASHERS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BOTTOM FAN SHROUD MOUNT BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BOTTOM FAN SHROUD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove three bolts and washers from the bottom fan shroud.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bottom fan shroud from radiator.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fan Shroud - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the bottom fan shroud on the radiator.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure bottom fan shroud with three washers and bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202110">Figure 14, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>). Torque bolts to 13 to 14 lbf-ft (18 to
                    19 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install nuts, washers, and bolts in stay rods and stay rod mount brackets, on both sides
                    of the radiator (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202109">Figure 13</hotlnk>). The P-clamp for the surge tank hose must be secured
                    to the bolt at the right stay rod. Torque bolts to 66 to 85 lbf-ft (90 to 115 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the radiator fan on the fan drive.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install six washers, lock washers, and nuts on the radiator fan (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202108">Figure 12</hotlnk>). Torque nuts to 25 lbf-ft (34 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the top fan shroud on the bottom fan shroud and engage the three plastic hold tabs
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202107">Figure 11, Item 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the top fan shroud with two washers and bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202107">Figure 11, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>). Torque bolts to 13 to 14 lbf-ft (18 to
                    19 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install left charge air cooler hose and secure two spring clamps (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202106">Figure 10, Items 2 and 3</hotlnk>). Torque spring clamps to 6 lbf-ft (8 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position surge tank on cooling package and secure with two nuts and one bolt (
                    <hotlnk document="s12021_13.xml" xrefid="f1202103">Figure 7, Items 2 and 3</hotlnk>). Torque nuts
                    and bolt to 13 to 14 lbf-ft (18 to 19 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the A/C condenser on the bottom mount bracket, make sure the A/C condenser is
                    seated properly on the bottom mount bracket (
                    <hotlnk document="s12021_14.xml" xrefid="f1202104">Figure 8, Items 4 and 8</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the A/C condenser top mount brackets on the top channel plate and secure with two
                    washers and nuts (
                    <hotlnk document="s12021_14.xml" xrefid="f1202104">Figure 8, Items 6 and 7</hotlnk>). Torque nuts to
                    13 to 14 lbf-ft (18 to 19 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install nut on P-clamps securing the A/C lines to the top channel plate and tighten (
                    <hotlnk document="s12021_14.xml" xrefid="f1202104">Figure 8, Items 1 and 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close and latch the hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
